    <b style="font-size:20px; color: coral;">Description: </b><br /><span id="MainContent_L10" style="font-size:Medium;"><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Advanced glycation end products (AGEs) accumulate with age and are key indicators of aging and disease. They disrupt mitochondrial function and block cellular energy production; they accelerate free radical accumulation and reduce the production of antioxidant enzymes; they cause protein cross-linking and degeneration in normal tissue, resulting in the aging and abnormality of mitochondria, blood vessels, bones, skin, eyes, liver and lungs.</p>
&nbsp; &nbsp; <b>Anti-AGEs Enhanced Formula Softgels - It can comprehensively prevent AGEs damage and boost cell vitality.</b><br /><br />
1. Inhibit the formation of AGEs<br />
<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; AGEs are the end products of nonenzymatic glycation, which are reversible in the early stages, whereas the advanced glycation end products are very stable once they are formed.<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; AGEs inhibitors act on the entire process of nonenzymatic glycation to prevent the production of glycated toxins, AGEs. The AGEs inhibitors block the production of early glycation products, reduce and eliminate intermediates in glycation reactions and prevent the highly reversible early glycation products from the formation of irreversible end products.</p>
2. Resist oxidation and reduce AGEs<br />
<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; The process of glycosylation is accompanied by the occurrence of oxidation. Studies have shown that antioxidants also have an inhibitory effect on the production of AGEs.<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; Antioxidants are involved in the process of oxidation to inhibit the formation of AGEs. Free radicals and peroxidation play an important role in the formation of AGEs. Good antioxidants inhibit glycation and reduce the production of AGEs.</p>
3. Accelerate the degradation of AGEs<br />
<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; With increasing age, AGEs production and accumulation of glycated toxins in serum and tissues are inevitable. The advanced glycation end products (AGEs) in the body are partially degraded by mononuclear macrophages, and the AGEs polypeptides formed by degradation are excreted through the kidney.<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; The immune enhancer can promote the activity of monocyte macrophage and accelerate the degradation and excretion of AGEs glycosylated toxin.</p>
4. Reduce AGEs damages<br />
<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Advanced glycation end products (AGEs) can cause damage to cells, mitochondria, and healthy tissues. The end products formed the glycosylated toxins, which are attached to healthy organs, lead to cross-linking of the originally ordered molecules, destroy the normal cell structure and mitochondrial function, become the cause of disease and aging.<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; Cytoprotective agents reduce AGEs damage to cells, mitochondria, normal proteins and tissues, protecting the body from injury.</p>
5. Enhance cell energy<br />
<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Mitochondria are the energy factories of cells. Ninety percent of the energy required by a cell comes from mitochondrial oxidative phosphorylation. AGEs disrupt the energy supply of mitochondria and block the production of cellular energy, which become the important cause of the aging process.<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; Energy booster can increase energy supply in the mitochondria, reverse the AGEs-induced energy production decrease in mitochondria, restore the normal function of mitochondria, enhance cell viability, and make the series of products more effective.</p></span><br />
    <b style="font-size:20px; color: coral;">Ingredients: </b><br /><span id="MainContent_L11" style="font-size:Medium;"><p><b>Formula contains 15 key active ingredients:</b><br />
Vitamin B6, L-Carnosine, Quercetin, Taurine, Alpha Lipoic acid, Olive Leaf Extract, Pomegranate Extract, Green Tea Extract, Chaga Mushroom Extract, Astragalus Root Extract, Resveratrol, Rosemary Extract, Turmeric Root Extract, L-Carnitines Proprietary Blend.</p>
<b>Vitamin B6</b>: VB6 blocks the formation of early glycation products and speeds up the oxidative degradation of early glycation, reducing AGEs formation.<br />
<b>L-Carnosine</b>: L-Carnosine has the similar structure with the proline lysine peptide, combine competitively with sugar decomposition products, reduce the content of reactive carbonyl, disrupt protein cross-linking process, and inhibit AGEs formation.<br />
<b>Quercetin</b>: Quercetin is an excellent inhibitor of nonenzymatic glycation in the early and intermediate stages.<br />
<b>Taurine</b>: Taurine blocks the highly reversible early glycation products from forming irreversible terminal products and effectively inhibits the production of AGEs glycosylated toxins.<br />
<b>Alpha Lipoic acid</b>: Alpha Lipoic acid inhibits the expression of AGEs receptors by inhibiting oxidative stress and reduces the damage caused by AGEs.<br />
<b>Olive leaf extract</b>: Olive leaf extract is effective against glycation and protects tissue against damage caused by AGEs glycation. The active component of the olive leaf extract is natural Iridoids, which is very rare in the conventional fruits and vegetables, and has a good therapeutic effect on aging, atherosclerosis, neurodegenerative diseases, and diabetes and so on.<br />
<b>Pomegranate extract</b>: Pomegranate extract can reduce the rate of oxidative reaction, inhibit the formation of AGEs, and coordinate with other AGEs inhibitors to better resist glycation reaction and delay aging. <br />
<b>Green tea extract</b>: Green tea extract has a good inhibitory effect on glycation reaction and protein cross-linking reaction, and reduces the formation of AGEs by inhibiting the oxidation process. <br />
<b>Chaga Mushroom Extract</b>: The extract of white deer antler contains a large number of three terpenoids and polysaccharides, which can promote the production of lymphocyte activating factor and enhance the immune activity of macrophage. The white birch extract comes from the primeval forest in Siberia and is called "the king of immunity".<br />
<b>Astragalus Root Extract</b>: Studies have shown that, Astragalus polysaccharides, which are rich in Astragalus Root Extract, can effectively reduce the production of AGEs and inhibit the expression of AGEs receptors, but also has multiple roles such as immune regulation, anti-oxidation, anti-inflammatory and so on.<br />
<b>Resveratrol</b>: Resveratrol can improve mitochondrial function, maintain cell energy supply, protect cell function and repair DNA damage of cells.<br />
<b>Rosemary extract</b>: Rosemary extract has a special effect on the cross-linking reaction in glycosylation. It can eliminate the cross linking products in proteins and reduce the cross-linking and denaturation induced by AGE in normal tissues.<br />
<b>Turmeric Root Extract</b>: Curcumin, which are rich in Turmeric Root Extract, can effectively reduce nonenzymatic glycation and oxidative stress, protect the nervous system, liver, kidney, cartilage tissue from glycation injury.<br />
<b>L-Carnitines Proprietary Blend</b>: they can provide cellular energy, reduce the accumulation of advanced glycation end products (AGEs), enhance cell viability, and make this formula more effective.<br /></span><br />
